        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(control-ui): add cron calendar timeline view",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a 24h timeline strip to the Cron Jobs page in the Control UI, providing an at-a-glance view of today's scheduled tasks.\n\nCloses #40644\n\n## Screenshots\n\n### Dark Theme — Full View\n![Full page dark](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/xvchris/cron-calendar-screenshots/main/dark-full.jpg)\n*Summary strip with always-on chip, 24h timeline with NOW indicator, cluster badges, color-coded dots*\n\n### Cluster Hover — Overlapping Jobs\n![Cluster hover](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/xvchris/cron-calendar-screenshots/main/cluster-hover.jpg)\n*Hovering the ④ cluster at 22:00 shows 4 overlapping jobs with color-coded dots and times*\n\n### Single Dot Hover — Job Info Popup\n![Dot hover](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/xvchris/cron-calendar-screenshots/main/dot-hover.jpg)\n*Hovering oss-scan dot shows schedule, status, duration, and \"Click → view run history\" hint*\n\n### Light Theme\n![Light theme](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/xvchris/cron-calendar-screenshots/main/light-theme.jpg)\n*Full light theme support via existing CSS variables*\n\n## Features\n\n### Timeline Strip\n- **24-hour timeline track** with grid lines and time labels\n- **NOW indicator** — red vertical line showing current time, auto-updates every 60s\n- **Color-coded dots** — each job gets a distinct color; green for past (ok), blue pulse for future (pending)\n- **Cluster badges** — nearby dots (within 2.5%) auto-merge into a numbered badge; hover to see the full list\n- **Hover popups** — JS-driven mouseenter/mouseleave with 150ms debounce for reliable hover behavior\n- **Click navigation** — past dots jump to Run History (filtered), future dots scroll to job details\n- **Zoom controls** — 24h (full day), Work (08:00–20:00), Now±3h (centered on current time)\n\n### Always-On Chips\n- High-frequency jobs (every <10min or cron `*/N` where N≤10) are displayed as chips in the summary strip instead of cluttering the timeline\n- Hover to see: View Details / View History / Run Now actions\n- Click to jump to run history\n\n### Other\n- **Mobile fallback** — timeline hidden on narrow screens, replaced by a simple text list of upcoming jobs\n- **Full i18n** — all strings use `t()`, translations added for en, zh-CN, zh-TW, de, es, pt-BR\n- **Theme support** — uses only existing CSS variables, works in both dark and light modes\n- **No existing features removed** — purely additive changes to the view layer\n\n## Files Changed\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `ui/src/ui/helpers/cron-timeline.ts` | **New** — Timeline computation (zoom, clustering, high-freq detection) |\n| `ui/src/ui/views/cron.ts` | Added timeline rendering between summary and workspace |\n| `ui/src/styles/components.css` | Added timeline CSS (523 lines) |\n| `ui/src/i18n/locales/*.ts` | Added `cron.timeline.*` keys to all 6 locales |\n\n## Testing\n\n- Computed timeline data from existing `CronProps` — no controller changes needed\n- All new code is additive; existing view functions untouched\n- TypeScript strict mode compatible\n\n---\n\n*AI Disclosure: This PR was authored with AI assistance (Claude). All code was reviewed and tested by a human.*",
